## Objective
- User is debugging why user-side (public) content and the navbar are not showing. Three prior complaints: (1) bulk-import not uploading, (2) subjects/content missing on user side, (3) "nothing showing up on the user side via the navbar." The navbar issue is now ROOT-CAUSED and FIXED.

## Important Details
- Workspace: `E:\Sikkhs` — Next.js 16 + Prisma 7.8.0 (libSQL/SQLite adapter, `DATABASE_URL=file:./db/custom.db`). Dev server on port 3000 (`next dev --turbopack -p 3000`), healthy.
- Content hierarchy hub: `/api/hierarchy/metadata` → `useHierarchyMetadata()` hook (client). Many user pages fetch their own `/api/...` endpoints.
- MIDDLEWARE GATE (`src/proxy.ts`): all `/api/*` NOT in `PUBLIC_API_ROUTES` (lines 14-59) require auth cookie → 401. `isPublicApiRoute` matches exact OR `route + '/'` prefix, so e.g. `/api/classes` also covers `/api/classes/[slug]`.
- CSRF: disabled locally via `ENABLE_CSRF=false` in `.env` + `CSRF_ENABLED` flag in `src/lib/csrf.ts` (prior task).
- DB engine mismatch (THE root cause of navbar blanks): several raw-SQL routes were written with **PostgreSQL-only syntax** (`::int`/`::bigint` casts, `= ANY($1::text[])`) but the app runs on **SQLite/libSQL**, which rejects `::` (`unrecognized token: ":"`) and `ANY(...)`. Confirmed via direct `tsx` repro. Note: `FILTER (WHERE …)` and `$1` placeholders DO work on libSQL.

